E%3Cli%3ELovable's%20CEO%20says%20long-term%20thinking%20and%20team-building%20culture%20are%20luring%20talent%20from%20Silicon%20Valley.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESweden's%20tech%20culture%20is%20%26quot%3Babout%20building%20for%20the%20coming%20decades%2C%26quot%3B%20Anton%20Osika%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOsika%20also%20cited%20the%20startup's%20%26quot%3Bhypergrowth%26quot%3B%20as%20another%20draw%20for%20foreign%20tech%20leaders.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EKeeping%20hold%20of%20tech%20talent%20can%20be%20a%20battle%20for%20European%20companies%2C%20but%20the%20CEO%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flovable-ceo-anton-osika-vibe-coding-creative-employees-work-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESwedish%20vibe-coding%20startup%20Lovable%3C%2Fa%3E%20says%20it's%20not%20always%20a%20one-way%20flow%20to%20Silicon%20Valley.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnton%20Osika%20said%20that%20what%20he%20considers%20a%20Swedish%20trait%20%E2%80%94%20long-term%20thinking%20and%20%26quot%3Bbuilding%20for%20the%20coming%20decades%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20is%20attracting%20some%20talent%20away%20from%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20Bloomberg%20interview%20that%20aired%20Friday%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EOsika%20said%20this%20longer-term%20mindset%2C%20paired%20with%20what%20he%20described%20as%20Sweden's%20tightly%20knit%2C%20low%20turnover%2C%20team-first%20culture%2C%20is%20luring%20some%20Swedish%20tech%20workers%20back%20from%20Silicon%20Valley%20and%20London.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20return%2C%20he%20said%2C%20because%20they%20%26quot%3Bmiss%20the%20way%20that%20we%20think%20about%20being%20here%20for%20the%20long%20term%20and%20everyone%20caring%20about%20the%20team%20performing%20really%20well%2C%20being%20very%20well-knit%20together%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20work%20ethos%20he%20said%20is%20embedded%20in%20Swedish%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22dffdac58-c288-4ac1-abbc-c0841257039c%5C%22%3EScaling%20fast%20from%20Stockholm%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELovable%2C%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faccel-to-lead-funding-round-for-lovable-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elaunched%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20November%202024%2C%20reached%20%24100%20million%20in%20annual%20recurring%20revenue%20%E2%80%94%20a%20metric%20that%20reflects%20predictable%20subscription%20income%20%E2%80%94%20within%20just%20eight%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20surged%20by%20more%20than%2030%25%2C%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flovables-hit-400-million-arr-doubling-in-a-few-months-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%24300%20million%20to%20%24400%20million%20in%20a%20single%20month%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Lovable's%20chief%20revenue%20officer%2C%20Ryan%20Meadows%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider's%20Ben%20Bergman.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Fvideos%2F2026-03-13%2Flovable-ceo-on-sweden-being-a-tech-powerhouse-video%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBloomberg%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EOsika%20described%20the%20company's%20trajectory%20as%20%26quot%3Bhypergrowth%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20pace%20he%20said%20remains%20relatively%20%26quot%3Buncommon%26quot%3B%20in%20Sweden.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20momentum%20is%20bringing%20foreign%20tech%20leaders%20to%20Stockholm%20%E2%80%94%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20relocating%20with%20their%20families.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20in%20this%20for%20the%20long%20term%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20Sweden's%20strong%20capital%20markets%20and%20deep%20talent%20pool%20are%20helping%20the%20company%20%26quot%3Bpunch%20above%20our%20weight.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Sweden%20has%20struggled%20to%20retain%20many%20of%20its%20biggest%20tech%20successes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20McKinsey%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mckinsey.com%2Fse%2Four-insights%2Fthe-paradoxes-of-swedens-success-and-struggles-and-the-path-forward%23%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20last%20August%20found%20that%20more%20than%2070%25%20of%20the%20country's%20unicorns%2C%20startups%20valued%20at%20%241%20billion%20or%20more%2C%20ultimately%20leave%20Sweden%2C%20typically%20through%20foreign%20acquisitions%20or%20listings%20abroad.%20Two%20of%20Sweden's%20most%20notable%20tech%20success%20stories%2C%20Klarna%20and%20Spotify%2C%20both%20opted%20to%20go%20public%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2256aea92b-52cb-422b-a757-863505c3559a%5C%22%3EWhat%20Europe%20can%20learn%20from%20Sweden%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOsika%20said%20that%20Sweden's%20other%20strength%20is%20the%20support%20new%20talent%20receives%20from%20the%20next%20wave%20of%20entrepreneurs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20lot%20of%20how%20previous%20founders%20help%20the%20new%20generation%20of%20founders%2C%26quot%3B%20Osika%20said.%20%26quot%3BOf%20course%2C%20there's%20a%20lot%20of%20this%20in%20Silicon%20Valley%20%E2%80%94%20and%20there's%20also%20that%20here%20in%20Stockholm.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESwedish%20startups%20are%20also%20forced%20to%20think%20internationally%20from%20day%20one%20because%20the%20domestic%20market%20is%20small%2C%20pushing%20founders%20to%20build%20for%20global%20scale%20almost%20immediately%2C%20which%20he%20said%20is%20different%20for%20some%20of%20the%20larger%20European%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20Osika%20said%20Sweden%20could%20move%20faster%2C%20especially%20in%20public-sector%20tech%20innovation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20like%20to%20see%20ambition%20and%20urgency%20from%20leaders%2C%20political%20leaders%2C%20and%20institutional%20leaders%20to%20reimagine%20what%20is%20possible%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20this%20urgency%20could%20be%20higher%20in%20Sweden%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20it's%20lacking%20in%20Europe%20at%20large%2C%20for%20sure.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20ori