%3Bmove%20fast%20and%20break%20things%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20ethos%20is%20proving%20to%20be%20literal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20week%2C%20Business%20Insider%20reported%20that%20Amazon%20set%20up%20new%20guardrails%20following%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-tightens-code-controls-after-outages-including-one-ai-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eseries%20of%20outages%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20one%20primarily%20driven%20by%20its%20AI%20coding%20tool%20that%20led%20to%20nearly%20120%2C000%20lost%20orders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimilar%20flubs%20have%20plagued%20other%20companies%20as%20they%20adopt%20AI.%20In%20January%2C%20an%20events%20company%20founder%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.saastr.com%2Fwe-built-an-ai-vp-of-marketing-this-year-heres-what-it-actually-does%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20an%20AI%20agent%20made%20four%20errors%20in%20a%20single%20week%2C%20including%20giving%20away%20free%20tickets.%20And%20last%20summer%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freplit-ceo-apologizes-ai-coding-tool-delete-company-database-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebrowser-based%20coding%20platform%20apologized%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20an%20AI%20agent%20wiped%20out%20a%20client's%20codebase%20and%20lied%20about%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20incidents%20highlight%20a%20delicate%20balancing%20act%20for%20employers%20eager%20to%20harness%20AI.%20Clamp%20down%20too%20hard%20on%20workers%2C%20and%20experimentation%20suffers.%20Loosen%20the%20reins%20too%20much%2C%20and%20the%20risks%20of%20errant%20AI%20agents%20or%20poorly%20reviewed%20code%20can%20quickly%20multiply.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20have%20to%20know%20your%20own%20risk%20tolerance%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Matt%20Rosenbaum%2C%20a%20principal%20researcher%20at%20The%20Conference%20Board%2C%20a%20nonprofit%20provider%20of%20data%20and%20insights%20for%20business%20leaders.%20%26quot%3BYou%20also%20have%20to%20know%20what%20to%20do%20if%20things%20go%20wrong%20and%20what%20to%20change%20so%20it%20doesn't%20happen%20again.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f7db8998-a17e-4f01-9a41-192552aadc9b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESpeed%20and%20power%2C%20unchecked%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20the%20challenge%20is%20that%20software%20developers%20aren't%20expected%20to%20write%20as%20much%20code%20as%20they%20used%20to%2C%20said%20Todd%20Olson%2C%20CEO%20and%20cofounder%20of%20Pendo%2C%20an%20AI%20startup%20that%20helps%20companies%20improve%20their%20user%20experience.%20Now%2C%20a%20large%20part%20of%20developers'%20jobs%20has%20shifted%20to%20reviewing%20code%20that%20is%20written%20by%20AI%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThose%20are%20very%20different%20skill%20sets%20and%20different%20habits%2C%26quot%3B%20Olson%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20problem%3A%20Since%20AI%20can%20generate%20code%20in%20seconds%2C%20workers%20racing%20to%20meet%20deadlines%20may%20be%20tempted%20to%20accept%20the%20output%20at%20face%20value%2C%20increasing%20the%20risk%20that%20mistakes%20slip%20through.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERoughly%20two-thirds%20of%20workers%20have%20accepted%20AI-generated%20output%20without%20carefully%20checking%20it%2C%20and%2072%25%20have%20put%20less%20effort%20into%20their%20tasks%20because%20of%20AI%2C%20according%20to%20a%20global%20study%20by%20KPMG%20and%20the%20University%20of%20Melbourne.%20The%20findings%20are%20based%20on%20a%20survey%20of%20more%20than%2030%2C000%20workers%20between%20November%202024%20and%20January%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20lesson%20companies%20are%20learning%20is%20that%20speed%20without%20analytic%20discipline%20at%20scale%20can%20create%20systemic%20exposure%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Lauren%20Buitta%2C%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20Girl%20Security%2C%20a%20nonprofit%20that%20prepares%20young%20women%20for%20careers%20in%20national%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20uncertainty%20surrounding%20AI's%20rapidly%20expanding%20capabilities%20adds%20another%20layer%20of%20complexity.%20As%20tools%20become%20more%20powerful%20and%20accessible%2C%20employees%20may%20test%20their%20limits%20without%20fully%20grasping%20the%20downstream%20consequences.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BJust%20because%20you%20can%20do%20something%20doesn't%20mean%20you%20should%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Kevin%20Serwatka%2C%20founder%20of%20the%20recruiting-intelligence%20platform%20Benchmarket%2C%20who%20previously%20worked%20in%20recruiting%20leadership%20roles%20at%20companies%20such%20as%20Google%2C%20Meta%2C%20and%20Robinhood.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20takeaway%20from%20these%20mistakes%2C%20he%20said%2C%20isn't%20to%20discourage%20experimentation%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20put%20guardrails%20around%20what%20that%20looks%20like%20at%20your%20company.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221eb4547d-da58-4d4e-bfb1-0f09edbf6b39%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20silver%20lining%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOlson%20said%20Amazon's%20outage%20also%20likely%20served%20as%20a%20learning%20lesson%20for%20the%20company%2C%20albeit%20a%20painful%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20just%20probably%20found%20a%20whole%20bunch%20of%20test%20cases%20that%20they%20can%20train%20AI%20on%2C%20so%20that%20the%20AI%20can%20review%20these%20things%20in%20the%20future%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20companies%20using%20AI%20to%20write%20code%20are%20likely%20to%20make%20mistakes%2C%20too%2C%20and%20that's%20a%20natural%20part%20of%20experimentation%2C%20said%20Andrew%20Filev%2C%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20coding%20agent%20company%20Zencoder.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSmall%20snafus%20are%20actually%20good%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20though%20ideally%20they're%20identified%20and%20addressed%20internally%20rather%20than%20exposed%20to%20customers.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20will%20learn%20and%20improve%20their%20guardrails%20and%20systems.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReminding%20workers%20of%20the%20importance%20of%20speaking%20up%20about%20any%20errors%20AI%20dishes%20out%20is%20critical%2C%20said%20Filev%2C%20because%20if%20a%20problem%20is%20ignored%2C%20it%20could%20lead%20to%20an%20%26quot%3Bincident%20where%20the%20blast%20radius%20is%20much%20bigger.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFilev%20said%20achieving%20AI%20autonomy%20requires%20starting%20with%20a%20combination%20of%20AI%20and%20human%20audits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20want%20both%20processes%20to%20work%20in%20parallel%20for%20a%20period%20of%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20until%20%26quot%3Bthe%20AI%20review%20is%20at%20least%20as%20good%20as%20the%20human%20review.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-challenges-companies-fast-paced-innovation-strategy-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1773395401000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69b1efe64d65ec517529de2b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-challenges-companies-fast-paced-innovation-strategy-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Companies%20are%20confronting%20a%20delicate%20balancing%20act%20as%20they%20try%20to%20scale%20AI%20without%20making%20costly%20mistakes.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22sneedleman%40businessinsider.com%20(Sarah%20E.%20Needleman%2CAna%20Altchek)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-challenges-companies-fast-paced-innovation-strategy-2026-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Arctic%20is%20stress-testing%20US%20Marines%20and%20their%20HIMARS%20in%20the%20most%20brutal%20conditions%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226153%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22US%20Marines%20with%202nd%20Battalion%2C%2010th%20Marine%20Regiment%2C%202nd%20Marine%20Division%2C%20launch%20a%20High%20Mobility%20Artillery%20Rocke