en%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69b37c174d65ec517529f272%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221344%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAnni%20Chen%20says%20she%20sees%20firsthand%20how%20AI-assisted%20workflows%20behave%20not%20just%20in%20prototypes%20but%20under%20real-world%20scale.%3Cp%3EAnni%20Chen%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAn%20Amazon%20tech%20lead%20says%20she%20got%20promoted%20quickly%20by%20building%20AI%20products.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAnni%20Chen%20uses%20AI%20not%20just%20to%20code%2C%20but%20to%20integrate%20AI's%20output%20into%20products.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20laid%20out%20her%20top%20tips%20for%20vibe%20coding%20and%20what%20common%20AI%20coding%20mistakes%20to%20avoid%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Anni%20Chen%2C%20who%20has%20worked%20in%20Amazon%20software%20engineering%20for%20about%20three-and-a-half%20years.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%20Business%20Insider%20has%20verified%20her%20employment%20history.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20helped%20me%20code%2C%20but%20more%20importantly%2C%20it%20helped%20with%20turning%20it%20into%20products.%20It's%20the%20combination%20of%20grasping%20AI%20and%20translating%20it%20into%20scalable%20products%20that%20helped%20me%20get%20promoted%20faster.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20off%20as%20a%20Software%20Engineer%20I%2C%20an%20entry-level%20role%2C%20in%202022.%20I%20was%20in%20the%20recommendations%20team%20working%20on%20serving%20recommendation%20widgets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20two%20years%20ago%2C%20I%20started%20working%20on%20AI%20products%20on%20the%20side.%20That%20became%20huge%20and%20eventually%20spun%20off%20into%20its%20own%20team%2C%20which%20I'm%20a%20founding%20engineer%20of.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20promoted%20in%20the%20recommendations%20team%20to%20Software%20Engineer%20II%2C%20and%20then%20I%20got%20promoted%20in%20the%20current%20team%20to%20senior%20engineer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20focus%20on%20what%20we%20call%20memory%2C%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-tech-lead-vibe-coding-daily-resist-anni-chen-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epowers%20personalization%20%3C%2Fa%3Ein%20generative%20AI%20experiences%20across%20Amazon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22feff66db-0968-465b-849b-459ba3ccb6c5%5C%22%3EAI%20writes%2095%25%20of%20my%20code%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20using%20AI%20as%20a%20side%20project%20to%20generate%20engaging%20titles%20for%20recommendation%20widgets%20when%20ChatGPT%20and%20Claude%20emerged.%20I%20saw%20how%20powerful%20it%20is%20in%20generating%20something%20really%20creative.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20thinking%3A%20whenever%20I%20have%20a%20question%20or%20I%20want%20to%20code%20something%20up%2C%20I'll%20just%20ask%20AI%20for%20help%20first%20before%20I%20attempt%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20saw%20that%20the%20solution%20it%20came%20up%20with%20was%20leveling%20up%20my%20own%20code%2C%20and%20it%20helped%20me%20code%20more%2C%20too.%20Now%20I%20would%20say%20almost%2095%25%20of%20the%20code%20authored%20by%20me%20is%20written%20by%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20not%20just%20using%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-ai-teach-teenagers-vibe-coding-kids-family-tech-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAI%20to%20code%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20I%20also%20integrate%20AI's%20output%20into%20products.%20I%20need%20to%20have%20a%20deep%20understanding%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fclawdbot-creator-vibe-coding-rabbit-hole-obsessed-openclaw-peter-steinberger-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehow%20AI%20works%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20what%20works%20well%2C%20and%20what%20doesn't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20to%20be%20open%20and%20receptive%20to%20new%20models%20and%20tools%20coming%20out%20that%20can%20help%20with%20product%20iterations%20and%20make%20products%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20work%20as%20a%20tech%20lead%20on%20large-scale%20LLM-driven%20systems%20in%20production%20environments%2C%20so%20I%20have%20a%20front-row%20seat%20to%20how%20AI-assisted%20workflows%20behave%2C%20not%20just%20in%20prototypes%20but%20under%20real-world%20scale%20and%20cross-team%20collaboration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225100c001-f3af-4b73-a4bd-fe461dd85e40%5C%22%3ETop%20tips%20for%20vibe%20coding%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20tip%20is%20understanding%20the%20inner%20workings%20of%20LLMs%20and%20where%20they%20might%20fail.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELLMs%20are%20pre-trained%20%E2%80%94%20they're%20trained%20on%20a%20large%20corpus%2C%20and%20it's%20a%20probabilistic%20game.%20It's%20followed%20by%20supervised%20fine-tuning%2C%20so%20the%20model%20will%20answer%20based%20on%20the%20structuring%20of%20a%20question%20and%20the%20answering%20format.%20Lastly%2C%20it's%20followed%20by%20RLHF%20%E2%80%94%20reinforcement%20learning%20from%20human%20feedback.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20understanding%20these%20three%20steps%2C%20you%20can%20know%2C%20for%20example%2C%20when%20the%20LLM%20will%20not%20understand%20what%20you're%20talking%20about%2C%20and%20when%20it%20needs%20domain%20knowledge%20from%20you.%20You%20will%20know%20when%20to%20use%20a%20new%20window%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-product-manager-vibe-coding-superpowers-non-technical-builder-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ewhy%20hallucinations%20happen.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20understanding%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fclaude-code-creator-vibe-coding-limits-boris-cherny-anthropic-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20limitations%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20context%20window%2C%20you%20know%20when%20to%20break%20problems%20down.%20You%20will%20learn%20how%20to%20follow%20the%20structure%20to%20break%20things%20down%20into%20lower%20levels%2C%20and%20then%20you%20slowly%20focus%20on%20each%20component%20and%20generate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20understanding%20the%20inner%20workings%2C%20you%20also%20know%20that%20you%20have%20to%20explain%20things%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnon-technical-people-vibecoding-lessons-ai-apps-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eto%20a%20peer.%3C%2Fa%3E%20If%20you%20don't%20explain%20in%20detail%2C%20it%20will%20default%20all%20those%20assumptions%20to%20the%20most%20common%20pattern%2C%20but%20that%20might%20not%20fit%20your%20use%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20second%20tip%3A%20Think%20before%20vibe%20coding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20check%20the%20answer%20first%2C%20then%20your%20thoughts%20will%20be%20swayed%20by%20the%20answers.%20Compare%20your%20thoughts%20versus%20the%20LLM's%20and%20see%20what%20the%20gaps%20are%20%E2%80%94%20what%20you%20didn't%20know%2C%20and%20why%20the%20answer%20differs.%20From%20there%2C%20you%20know%20what%20implicit%20assumptions%20you%20haven't%20told%20the%20LLM.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThirdly%2C%20prompt%20for%20hard%20questions.%20Ask%20questions%20like%20what%20is%20the%20fallback%20when%20there%20is%20an%20error%2C%20or%20how%20this%20is%20going%20to%20scale%3F%20This%20is%20like%20a%20teacher%20asking%20a%20student%2C%20or%20a%20senior%20engineer%20asking%20a%20junior%20engineer%20to%20make%20sure%20the%20hard%20cases%20are%20covered.%20If%20you%20want%20the%20product%20to%20scale%2C%20think%20about%20it%20from%20day%20one%20and%20be%20conscious%20about%20asking%20those%20scaling%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELastly%2C%20review%20and%20understand.%20Always%20review%20at%20each%20step%2C%20not%20just%20review%20after%20the%20whole%20code%20is%20generated.%20This%20ensures%20errors%20stop%20early%20rather%20than%20cascading%20all%20the%20way%20to%20the%20end%2C%20where%20you%20need%20to%20redo%20everything.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECreating%20wrong%20code%20is%20very%20dangerous.%20The%20presence%20of%20code%20makes%20people%20think%2C%20%26quot%3BOkay%2C%20this%20is%20good%2C%20it's%20working.%26quot%3B%20But%20wrong%20code%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-ai-ceo-vibe-coding-software-replace-apps-mustafa-suleyman-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eenters%20production%20%3C%2Fa%3Ecan%20cause%20more%20damage%20than%20the%20absence%20of%20functionality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e87b9d9f-c136-4b6b-82b2-8b4073df0eb7%5C%22%3EUnderstanding%20code%20is%20still%20important%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20have%20to%20understand%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fexecutives-weigh-in-on-learn-to-code-advice-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eyour%20own%20code%3C%2Fa%3E.%20AI%20lowers%20the%20barrier%20to%20writing%20code%2C%20but%20not%20the%20responsibility%20for%20understanding%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20something%20goes%20wrong%20and%20the%20code%20was%20committed%20by%20you%2C%20you're%20the%20one%20responsible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EImagine%20your%20code%20breaks%20in%20production%2C%20and%20you%20need%20to%20fix%20it%2C%20and%20you%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20also%20don't%20know%2C%20AI%20told%20me.%26quot%3B%20That's%20not%20the%20correct%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20think%20we%20can%20entrust%20AI%20with%20such%20high-stakes%20tasks%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnderstanding%20becomes%20easier%20with%20AI%20because%20it's%20also%20a%20perfect%20learning%20opportunity.%20You%20can%20simply%20open%20another%20window%20and%20ask%20it%20to%20explain%20the%20concept.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20ask%20in%20the%20same%20window%20about%20what%20it%20produced%2C%20it%20will%20explain%20only%20in%20that%20context.%20But%20you%20want%20to%20understand%20the%20concept%20more%20generally%20and%20see%20whether%20it%20makes%20sense%20to%20apply%20in%20this%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20have%20a%20story%20to%20share%20about%20coding%20with%20AI%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Acmlee%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_