s.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSince%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20war%2C%20we%20have%20been%20receiving%20daily%20requests%20from%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20whereas%20previously%20it%20might%20have%20been%20once%20or%20twice%20a%20month%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Jens%20Holzapfel%2C%20business%20development%20director%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnordic-air-defence-kreuger-100-ukraine-war-drone-shahed-orlan-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ENordic%20Air%20Defense%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20Swedish%20startup%20is%20building%20a%20propeller-driven%20interceptor%2C%20the%20Kreuger-100XR%2C%20which%20is%20being%20tested%20in%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20interest%20has%20overwhelmingly%20come%20from%20Gulf%20state%20governments%20or%20entities%20working%20with%20their%20defense%20ministries%2C%20although%20European%20countries%20have%20also%20reached%20out%2C%20the%20companies%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMisha%20Lu%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20Taiwanese%20firm%20Tron%20Future%2C%20said%20international%20inquiries%20for%20its%20counterdrone%20products%2C%20which%20include%20a%20single-use%20quadcopter%20interceptor%20and%20net-launcher%20drone%2C%20have%20%26quot%3Beffectively%20doubled%26quot%3B%20since%20the%20war%20began.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlmost%20all%20prospective%20clients%20were%20asking%20for%20ways%20to%20protect%20critical%20infrastructure%2C%20such%20as%20airports%20and%20power%20grids%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELu%20added%20that%20potential%20buyers%20are%20also%20largely%20shifting%20their%20focus%20from%20anti-drone%20jammers%20to%20%26quot%3Bhard-kill%26quot%3B%20solutions%2C%20which%20rely%20on%20explosives%20or%20physical%20force%20to%20destroy%20drone%20threats.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2272f75a73-becc-4b77-b0e9-df8dfd2de7c6%5C%22%3ESurging%20interest%20in%20Ukrainian%20drones%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHeightened%20demand%20for%20hard-kill%20counterdrone%20tech%20comes%20as%20Iran%20has%20launched%20thousands%20of%20one-way%20attack%20Shaheds%20against%20the%20US%20and%20its%20allies%20in%20the%20Gulf%20region.%20Some%20of%20the%20loitering%20munitions%20have%20successfully%20gotten%20through%20air%20defenses%20and%20struck%20their%20targets%2C%20including%20US%20military%20facilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKey%20concerns%20in%20air%20defense%20against%20Shahed%20threats%20have%20been%20cost%20and%20quantity.%20Traditional%20air-to-air%20or%20surface-to-air%20missiles%20are%20limited%20in%20supply%20and%20would%20be%20too%20expensive%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Firan-russia-now-us-one-style-drone-reshaping-moden-war-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eengage%20en%20masse%20against%20Shaheds%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20cost%20%2420%2C000%20to%20%2450%2C000%20each.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225458%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20Iranian%20Shahed%20drone%20sits%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20a%20room%20on%20Capitol%20Hill%20as%20congressional%20leaders%20make%20a%20presentation.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69b267d5a7a4f9df67ba3501%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223639%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Iranian%20Shahed%20has%20been%20a%20subject%20of%20Western%20concern%20for%20years%20as%20Russia%20used%20the%20drones%20to%20bombard%20Ukraine%2C%20but%20the%20recent%20war%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20has%20renewed%20concern%20about%20allied%20preparedness%20against%20the%20loitering%20munition.%3Cp%3EWin%20McNamee%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EA%20cheaper%20solution%2C%20pioneered%20largely%20by%20Ukraine%2C%20is%20to%20use%20first-person-view%20or%20small%20drones%20to%20catch%20and%20ram%20into%20Shaheds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Wild%20Hornets%2C%20the%20Ukrainian%20manufacturer%20of%20a%20popular%20interceptor%20drone%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcheap-drone-shahed-sting-wild-hornets-bullet-train-speed-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecalled%20the%20Sting%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20company%20previously%20fielded%20one%20or%20two%20business%20inquiries%20daily%2C%20but%20since%20last%20week%20has%20received%20%26quot%3Bseveral%20dozen%20per%20day.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESting%20production%20is%20still%20heavily%20dedicated%20to%20helping%20Ukraine%20fight%20off%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-new-turbojet-drone-geran-5-american-chinese-german-parts-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ERussia's%20locally%20built%20versions%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20Shahed%3B%20Kyiv%20says%20Moscow%20has%20launched%20over%2057%2C000%20of%20them%20so%20far.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20are%20requests%2C%20not%20what%20we've%20agreed%20to%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Wild%20Hornets%20spokesperson%20said%20of%20the%20new%20inquiries.%20%26quot%3BOur%20priority%20is%20Ukraine's%20defense.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20major%20Ukrainian%20drone%20maker%2C%20Skyfall%2C%20told%20Reuters%20last%20week%20that%20it%20was%20receiving%20foreign%20requests%20for%20interceptors%20and%20could%20export%20up%20to%2010%2C000%20a%20month%20without%20affecting%20Ukraine's%20needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20Ukrainian%20firms%20may%20have%20difficulty%20closing%20any%20such%20deals%20for%20now.%20A%20wartime%20law%20broadly%20blocks%20drone%20exports%20from%20the%20country%2C%20as%20uncrewed%20aerial%20systems%20remain%20the%20pillar%20of%20its%20tactical%20combat%20operations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Urkainian%20soldier%20holds%20a%20Sting%20interceptor%20drone%2C%20which%20has%20been%20decorated%20to%20resemble%20a%20shark.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69b2675da96e437d6eb82e97%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Wild%20Hornets%20manufacture%20the%20Sting%2C%20a%20popular%20interceptor%20drone%20now%20used%20in%20Ukraine.%3Cp%3EAlex%20Nikitenko%2FGlobal%20Images%20Ukraine%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20the%20ban%20will%20remain%2C%20however%2C%20is%20unclear.%20Kyiv%20has%20been%20exploring%20the%20possibility%20of%20controlled%20exports%2C%20seeking%20to%20promote%20its%20fledgling%20defense%20tech%20market%20and%20touting%20its%20wartime%20production%20expertise%20and%20ability%20to%20test%20weapons%20in%20combat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-interceptor-drone-shaheds-filed-requests-us-allies-iran-war-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EUkrainian%20President%20Volodymyr%20Zelenskyy%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20also%20repeatedly%20signaled%20openness%20to%20assisting%20allied%20countries%2C%20including%20Gulf%20States%2C%20that%20request%20support%20and%20expertise%20against%20Shaheds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20far%2C%20though%2C%20Zelenskyy%20has%20only%20confirmed%20that%20Kyiv%20is%20sending%20experts%20to%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20without%20mentioning%20export%20sales.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2202861bdc-3dc3-4aa6-a804-4c288e6e5a38%5C%22%3EToo%20much%20demand%20to%20cope%20with%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20interceptor%20makers%20in%20other%20countries%2C%20the%20sudden%20demand%20is%20so%20great%20that%20most%20aren't%20sure%20they%20can%20keep%20up%20with%20the%20influx%20of%20business.%20The%20technology%20is%20also%20fairly%20young%2C%20meaning%20some%20firms%20have%20yet%20to%20build%20out%20their%20production%20lines%20fully.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAgirs%20Kipurs%2C%20CEO%20of%20the%20Latvia-based%20firm%20Origin%20Robotics%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20his%20firm%20is%20already%20working%20to%20fulfill%20existing%20contracts%20and%20may%20thus%20only%20meet%20a%20%26quot%3Blimited%20part%20of%20the%20demand.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BObviously%2C%20we%20will%20not%20be%20able%20to%20meet%20all%20requests%2C%20as%20we%20are%20still%20scaling%20up%20production%20and%20building%20toward%20full%20output%20capacity%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Kipurs%2C%20whose%20firm%20builds%20drones%20deployed%20in%20Ukraine%20and%20an%20autonomous%20interceptor%20used%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffront-line-nato-forces-train-operate-survive-drones-ukraine-threat-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ENATO%20forces.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJi%C5%99%C3%AD%20Janou%C5%A1ek%2C%20a%20representative%20for%20the%20Czech%20firm%20TRL%20Drones%2C%20said%20his%20company%20recently%20received%20multiple%20requests%20a%20day%20for%20its%20fixed-wing%20interceptors%20%E2%80%94%20a%20short-range%20drone%20and%20a%20larger%20jet-powered%20system%20that%20are%20used%20in%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETRL%20Drones%20is%20increasing%20production%20capacity%20to%20accommodate%20new%20requests%2C%20Janou%C5%A1ek%20said%2C%20but%20has%20had%20to%20%26quot%3Bcarefully%20prioritize%20incoming%20opportunities%2C%26quot%3B%20giving%20preference%20to%20customers%20who%20already%20know%20their%20operational%20requirements%20and%20are%20ready%20to%20move%20quickly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSupporting%20Ukraine%20remains%20a%20core%20priority%20that%20continues%20to%20utilize%20a%20portion%20of%20our%20capacity%2C%26quot%3B%20Janou%C5%A1ek%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELu%2C%20of%20Tron%20Future%2C%20said%20that%20his%20firm%20is%20%26quot%3Bfully%20engaged%26quot%3B%20with%20all%20the%20inquiries%20it's%20receiving%2C%20but%20is%20still%20working%20on%20scaling%20production.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222048%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20quadcopter%20interceptor%20built%20by%20Tron%20Future%20sits%20on%20display.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69b26701a7a4f9df67ba34fe%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221112%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOne%20of%20Tron%20Future's%20interceptors%20on%20display%20at%20an%20aerospace%20and%20defense%20show%20in%20Taipei.%3Cp%3ETron%20Future%3C%2Fp%3E%